## Gate A Overview
<!-- Gate A confirms that the project initiation phase is complete. It validates that the problem and vision are clearly defined, feasibility has been assessed, key risks are understood, and there is sufficient justification and organisational commitment to proceed to Phase 2 (Planning). -->

Gate A validates:
- The problem and vision are clearly defined and agreed by key stakeholders
- Feasibility has been assessed across technical, data, AI/ML, organisational, financial, and legal dimensions
- Key stakeholders are identified, engaged, and communication plans are in place
- Initial risks are captured and top risks have mitigation plans
- A Project Charter has been produced and signed off
- There is a clear decision to PROCEED / HOLD / KILL

